  "text": "Mortality 28 days after admission was at around 35%, well above the 1.3% expected by PELOD. Survival could be influenced by organ failure, immunocompromise and perhaps by the development of complications associated to the ventilatory strategies employed. It is also known that many models (PIM, PIM2, PRISM) underestimate mortality [CITATION_1] [22] . We used the PELOD score but could not say it underestimates mortality as well, as only a subpopulation of children admitted to the PICU was studied. Besides, this study did not aim to evaluate correlation and agreement between predicted and actual mortality by PELOD.",
